Let us use the formula from step 4 to compute the number of ex-rights shares. This is computed as follows:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Number of ex-rights shares }&=\dfrac{\text{26,000,000}}{\text{\$70,000,000.00 $\div$ S}}\\[10pt]
&={\textbf{0.3714S}}
\end{aligned}$$ 

**The number of ex-rights shares is 0.3714S.** We will use this value in the subsequent step.

Now, let us divide both sides by 2.857 to cancel out the coefficient of S. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\dfrac{\text{ 2.857S }}{\text{2.857}}&=\dfrac{\text{\$63.00}}{\text{2.857}}\\[10pt]
{\text{S}}&={\textbf{\$22.05}}
\end{aligned}$$
